               <p>MARY FELTS. I am servant to William Elliott - he is a <rs id="t18300415-263-viclabel1457" type="occupation">tobacconist</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-263-victim2288 t18300415-263-viclabel1457"></join>. On the 17th of March the prisoner came into his shop, and asked the price of some tobacco; he was told the price, and while Mr. Elliott turned away, he stole a penknife off the counter, took it out of the shop, and gave it to another boy - I called the Police-officer, and brought the prisoner back; it was a good knife.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-263-person2289">
                  THOMAS 
                  MIDDLETON
               <interp inst="t18300415-263-person2289" type="surname" value="MIDDLETON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-263-person2289" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-263-person2289" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the officer I took the prisoner; I found 1s. 6 1/2d. on him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went and asked the price of tobacco, came out, and went about a hundred yards; this lady came and said I had stolen a penknife - I said "I will go back."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-263-verdict1458" type="verdictDescription">
